# MCP payloads — inline only (Cursor rule — short form)

Applies to **every** agent session in this repository.

## Must follow

1. Put inline tool arguments (`use_figma` → `code`, etc.) **in the tool call**, not in throwaway repo files (no `.mcp-*`, `*-payload.json`, `_tmp*`, scratch under `skills/`).
2. If too large, use **multiple sequential** self-contained tool calls — not chained via staging files on disk.
3. **Committed** paths named by `SKILL.md` / phase files (e.g. `skills/create-design-system/canvas-templates/bundles/*.min.mcp.js`, `skills/create-component/templates/*.figma.js`) — `Read` those and pass contents inline; do **not** duplicate into a staging copy.
4. **Canvas bundles** (create-design-system Steps 15a–15c + 17; sync-design-system 6.Canvas.9b / 9d): parent uses **`Task` → [`skills/canvas-bundle-runner/SKILL.md`](../../skills/canvas-bundle-runner/SKILL.md)** — parent must **not** `Read` `.min.mcp.js` or call `use_figma` for those redraws. After each Task, parent runs [`skills/create-design-system/conventions/14-audit.md`](../../skills/create-design-system/conventions/14-audit.md) § *After canvas-bundle-runner (parent thread)*.
5. **Non-canvas** `use_figma`: build inline `code` in the parent; ~50k cap; no shell `cat` of huge files as source of truth (truncation risk).

**Full rationale, exceptions, host matrix, table fidelity:** [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md).
